criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  live in Australia;

          -  are aged 45 years or over;

          -  have experienced activity-related knee pain during the past 3 months or have been told
             by a health professional that they have knee OA, ; and

          -  are able to easily understand verbal and written English language.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  have had a hip or knee joint replacement;

          -  are scheduled/referred to see an orthopaedic surgeon or are already on a waiting list
             for hip or knee joint replacement;

          -  have any type of systemic arthritis (e.g. rheumatoid arthritis, gout), or have morning
             stiffness that lasts longer than 30 minutes;

          -  have a health condition that makes them unable to walk (since it will be difficult for
             people who cannot walk to follow the recommendations made in either video);

          -  have seen a health professional for their knee pain during the previous six months
